<LP>
   ATLANTA -- First Financial Management Corp. said it agreed
to acquire an Atlanta-based debt-collection company for about
$65 million.
   First Financial said it will purchase Nationwide Credit
for 1.3 million shares of First Financial common stock and
$31.8 million in cash.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Nationwide Credit provides services to financial
institutions, retailers, government agencies anbd health-care
providers and had more than $30 million in revenue in 1989.
First Financial is an information-services company.
</TEXT>
